Everything here is really good!  I was taken back at the quality of this Mexican Food in Washington Heights. Reasonably priced and lots of options besides tacos and burritos.  One of my favorites is their Dominican/Mexican fusion: Tostones a la Mexicana. Think Nachos but with Fried Plantains and your choice of meat, comes with pico de gallo and mexican cheese. Delicious!!  Favorite Meats here, Al Pastor, Chorizo, Carnitas, Steak.  Give this hidden gem a try if you are in the Washington Heights area.

(Translated by Google) I decided to go out with my children to try the famous Mexican cakes. I chose this small restaurant to support Washington Heights merchants. This was the worst decision. I observed how kind he was with the Mexican clients who entered the premises and I came to the obvious conclusion, ha .... I AM NOT MEXICAN. What a shame that we treat ourselves like this. 😔 Going back to Top Up ...  (Original) Decidí salir con mis  hijos a probar las famosas tortas mexicanas.
